00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:05.170
with a score by Carlos Chavez.

00:01:05.170 --> 00:01:09.360
And this week we'll be sharing with
our audiences a beautiful video

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.210
of a brand-ew Library of
Congress dance commission

00:01:12.210 --> 00:01:14.900
from Swedish choreographer
Pontus Lindberg,

00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:17.320
set to music by Irving Fine.

00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:21.890
So check out our website
next week for a preview.

00:01:21.890 --> 00:01:25.600
Tonight we are very, very delighted
to have Hayden Herrera here

00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:29.970 position:56%
to offer us a scholar's introduction
to the eloquent and poetic work

00:01:29.970 --> 00:01:33.210
of Isamu Noguchi, who
created sets for all three

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:36.140
of the Martha Graham
ballets in the festival.

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:39.060
The profound connection
between Graham and Noguchi,

00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:43.150
one of the most influential artists
of the 20th century, is in fact one

00:01:43.150 --> 00:01:45.120
of the program threads
for the festival,

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:47.370
as you'll see in the
program booklet you have.

00:01:47.370 --> 00:01:51.170
Miss Herrera has received
critical acclaim for her biography

00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:55.870
of Noguchi, who commented that
dancers brought his sets to life.

00:01:55.870 --> 00:01:59.740
"Then the air becomes charged
with meaning and emotion,

00:01:59.740 --> 00:02:02.090
and form plays its integral part

00:02:02.090 --> 00:02:05.600
in a reenactment of
a ritual," he wrote.

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:09.710
"Theater is a ceremonial,
the performance is a rite.

00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:14.350
Sculpture in daily life
should or could be like this.

00:02:14.350 --> 00:02:16.870
They move, and the world moves."

00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:20.130
Miss Herrera has also been
admired for her biographies

00:02:20.130 --> 00:02:22.200
of two other great
modernist figures,

00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:24.510
Frida Kahlo and Arshile Gorky.

00:02:24.510 --> 00:02:27.950
After her talk,she'll be
signing copies of her book

00:02:27.950 --> 00:02:29.400
and it will also be available

00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:31.740
in the Library sale shop
during our festival.

00:02:31.740 --> 00:02:34.950
So we hope you'll join us
this week for more events.

00:02:34.950 --> 00:02:38.510
And now please join me in
welcoming Hayden Herrera.

00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:43.280
